The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Ranatunga in hospital

 Ranatunga 

Colombo: Sri Lanka?s World Cup winning captain 

Arjuna Ranatunga was on Wednesday hospitalised with a heart ailment, a family 

friend said. 

Ranatunga, who led Sri Lanka to an epic triumph in 

the 1996 World Cup, was rushed to a private hospital, the friend said. 

He also added that the former captain was under observation following dizziness. 

The 41-year-old Ranatunga is also the deputy minister for industry, tourism and investment promotion. 

Ranatunga, Wisden Cricketer of the Year in 1999, scored 5105 runs in 93 Tests and 7456 from 269 ODIs. 

